Definition: Material sample ID with _r1/2 (sequencing, i.e., technical replicate 1/2) and _s1/2 (biological, i.e. sample replicate 1/2) appended
ENA run accession number for the 18S sequence
ENA run accession number for the  negative control18S sequence
ENA run accession number for the COI sequence
ENA run accession number for the negative control COI sequence
ENA run accession number for the ITS sequence
ENA run accession number for the  negative control ITS sequence
Material Sample ID as written on the shipped samples
Information about why sequencing was repeated (where relevant)
As sequencing runs were sometimes repeated, but previous runs retained, this contains the repeat value (first, second, etc) of the run

Data type: s2 if the second sample replicate (only a few sample replicates were used)"
